<div><h3>PSYC 221 - Research in Social Psychology </h3>  <p><hr><strong>Fall 2019: </strong>This course provides undergraduate students with the opportunity to conduct research on topics in social justice. Students in this course will have the opportunity to participate in various projects related to a) conflict and peace processes (e.g., disadvantaged groups&#8217; attitudes towards reconciliation and forgiveness) and b) collective action and social movements (e.g., the role of advantaged group members in social movements). Students will be responsible for a variety of research tasks, including, but not limited to, data collection, data entry, data coding, data analysis, and scientific writing. This course may be repeatable for credit.</p>

<p>Prerequisites for this course require a grade of C- or better</p>

